{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782105201081,"sessionID":"ses_1124778f7ffeJhjpxd57xv8T9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_f840be06e95749219b87953f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/benchmark-runs/flaky-retry/workspaces/h3c3-cc6a58dd/README.md","content":"# Temperature Conversion Package\n\nConvert temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin using a CLI.\n\n## CLI Usage\n```bash\npython cli.py <value> --to-fahrenheit\npython cli.py <value> --to-kelvin\n```\n\nExamples:\n- Convert 100°C to Fahrenheit: `python cli.py 100 --to-fahrenheit`\n- Convert 0°C to Kelvin: `python cli.py 0 --to-kelvin`\n\n## Package Structure\n- `converters.py`: Core conversion functions\n- `cli.py`: Command-line interface\n- `test_converters.py`: Unit tests for converters\n- `test_cli.py`: Unit tests for CLI\n\nRequires a numeric value and one of the mutually exclusive flags. Input is assumed to be in Celsius."},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/benchmark-runs/flaky-retry/workspaces/h3c3-cc6a58dd/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"benchmark-runs/flaky-retry/workspaces/h3c3-cc6a58dd/README.md","time":{"start":1782105201078,"end":1782105201080}},"id":"prt_eedbf59b3001eOcHr5HFTfnDud","sessionID":"ses_1124778f7ffeJhjpxd57xv8T9Y","messageID":"msg_eedbddea200137Aupyb1MfTwpw"}}
